<h2 id="nav-offseting">
    Offseting columns
    <a href="#nav-offseting" class="anchor-link"></a>
</h2>

<p>You can use offsetting for specified device by using classes dedicated to mediums,
    example .col--*-offset-3, where * is one of mediums (phone, tablet, mobile, desktop, desktop-xl).</p>

<div class="code-example code-example--grid">
    <div data-clone>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-4 col--offset-4">.col-4 .col--offset-4</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-4">.col-4</div>
            <div class="col-4 col--offset-4">.col-4 .col--offset-4</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-6 col--offset-6">.col-6 .col--offset-6</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>

<h3>Reset offseting</h3>
<p>To reset offset use these classes:</p>
<ul class="list-unstyled">
    <li><code>.col--phone-offset-0</code></li>
    <li><code>.col--tablet-offset-0</code></li>
    <li><code>.col--mobile-offset-0</code></li>
    <li><code>.col--desktop-offset-0</code></li>
    <li><code>.col--desktop-xl-offset-0</code></li>
</ul>


